    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.29.35"/>
                <note type="curatorial">35</note>
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="authorial">
                    7912 NORTH KARLOV AVENUE 
                    SKOKIE 6, ILLINOIS
                </fw>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    I remember your first poem "Divine Enchantment" and how proud my partner was when you sent him a copy!! A.P.N.
                </note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Tuesday Feb. 7th, 1961</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John G. Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>R. D. 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </opener>
                
                <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                
                <p>Dear John: Your note concerning your vivid dream of Fred was so interesting and
                    such experiences are difficult of explanations.</p>
                <p>I am sending you a clipping from last Sundays "Letters to Editor" from our Chicago Tribune, you may have seen it but it was along your line-and maybe you can understand it all-(I'm frank to say I cannot). To you work so hard on your poems? So sorry I missed session of your birthday celebration and how old are you? Fred was 2 years older than I and shall be 75 my next birthday.  I think I read everything in Chigo Tribune, but that I missed. My daughter in law was in Arkansas and I was looking after family. So May have been careless at that time.</p>
                <p>May I wish for Mrs. Neihardt and you a comfortable 1961 and wish sincere regards to you both, I am</p>
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    <signed>Helena Pale Newton</signed>
                    
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
